// The example mod - the ONE copy-me tutorial mod. Copy this whole folder to
// start your own mod: it demonstrates a little of EVERYTHING a mod can do in a
// single, self-contained, playable package.
//
// A mod is the SAME folder-bundle shape as the base game: a `*.bundle.ron`
// manifest listing its content files (paths relative to THIS folder) plus a
// `meta` self-description (name/description/author/version..., what the Mods
// menu and details panel show), and optionally the binary assets it ships.
//
// What this bundle carries:
//   - content: one `*.content.ron` file. It OVERRIDES a base section by id, ADDS
//     a new section, ADDS a playable arena scenario, and ADDS a menu-backdrop
//     scenario - see the header of example.content.ron for the tour.
//   - resources: the binary files this mod ships itself (bundle-dir-relative,
//     the same base as `content` and `meta.icon`). Content references them with
//     `self://<path>`, which resolves against THIS folder - `mods/example/...`
//     when shipped, `mods://example/...` when downloaded from the portal. A
//     `self://` ref may only name a LISTED resource; the portal generator, the
//     static content lint and the runtime content gate all reject an undeclared
//     one. The skybox's `.meta` sidecar (nebula.png.meta) rides along
//     automatically and is NOT listed here.
//
// This mod is registered in `assets/mods.catalog.ron` (the installed-mods
// catalog) so it ships INSTALLED but disabled; enable it from the main-menu Mods
// section, or add its id to `EnabledMods`. `base` is an IMPLICIT dependency and
// is never declared.
(
    content: ["example.content.ron"],
    resources: [
        "textures/nebula.png",
        "textures/rock.png",
    ],
    meta: (
        name: "Example Mod",
        description: "The copy-me tutorial mod: a section overlay, a new section, a playable arena, mod-shipped art, and a menu backdrop - a little of everything.",
        author: "Nova Protocol",
        version: "1.0.0",
        // base is an implicit dependency and is never declared (see the header
        // comment); list only OTHER mods this one depends on. This mod has none.
        dependencies: [],
    ),
)
